WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.000
Smallville Arrival

00:03.000 --> 00:07.000
Based on a novelisation by Michael Taitelbaum

00:20.000 --> 00:21.000
Arrival

00:22.000 --> 00:26.000
Chapter 1 A child arrives

00:27.000 --> 00:32.000
1989 Smallville, Kansas, USA

00:33.000 --> 00:36.000
Suddenly the sky was dark

00:36.000 --> 00:39.000
There were hundreds of meteors in the sky

00:39.000 --> 00:42.000
They went faster and faster

00:43.000 --> 00:47.000
There was a very small spaceship in the centre of the meteors

00:48.000 --> 00:51.000
There was one person in this spaceship

00:51.000 --> 00:53.000
A child

00:54.000 --> 00:57.000
Nothing happened in Smallville

00:57.000 --> 01:00.000
It was a small town in Kansas

01:00.000 --> 01:03.000
And it was a very boring place

01:03.000 --> 01:07.000
Then one day everything changed

01:08.000 --> 01:13.000
Lionel Luther arrived from Metropolis in his helicopter

01:13.000 --> 01:15.000
He was a rich man

01:15.000 --> 01:17.000
But he was not a nice man

01:17.000 --> 01:20.000
He loved money, not people

01:21.000 --> 01:24.000
His young son Lex sat next to him

01:24.000 --> 01:27.000
Lex was nine years old

01:27.000 --> 01:30.000
He had red hair and blue eyes

01:30.000 --> 01:32.000
His face was white

01:32.000 --> 01:34.000
And his eyes were closed

01:34.000 --> 01:36.000
He was very frightened

01:37.000 --> 01:40.000
Lex shouted his father

01:40.000 --> 01:42.000
Open your eyes now

01:42.000 --> 01:44.000
I can't

01:44.000 --> 01:45.000
Lex said

01:45.000 --> 01:47.000
I hate this helicopter

01:48.000 --> 01:51.000
Luther's aren't frightened of anything

01:51.000 --> 01:52.000
Lionel said

01:52.000 --> 01:55.000
Look out of the window now

01:57.000 --> 02:00.000
Lex slowly opened his eyes and looked down

02:00.000 --> 02:02.000
I'm going to die

02:02.000 --> 02:04.000
He thought

02:05.000 --> 02:09.000
Two men waited for the helicopter in the car park of an old factory

02:09.000 --> 02:12.000
The men were brothers

02:12.000 --> 02:14.000
Dale and Bill Ross

02:15.000 --> 02:19.000
Why does Lionel Luther want to buy our factory?

02:19.000 --> 02:21.000
Ask Dale

02:21.000 --> 02:23.000
I don't know, said Bill

02:23.000 --> 02:26.000
But we need his money

02:26.000 --> 02:28.000
He isn't going to change anything

02:28.000 --> 02:30.000
He told us that

02:30.000 --> 02:32.000
And I believe him

02:33.000 --> 02:36.000
Jonathan Kent and his wife Martha

02:36.000 --> 02:39.000
went into a shop on Main Street

02:39.000 --> 02:42.000
Their faces were brown from the sun

02:42.000 --> 02:44.000
And their jeans were old

02:44.000 --> 02:46.000
They lived on a farm

02:46.000 --> 02:48.000
Afternoon, Nell

02:48.000 --> 02:50.000
Jonathan said

02:50.000 --> 02:52.000
Hello, Jonathan

02:52.000 --> 02:53.000
Nell said

02:53.000 --> 02:54.000
She smiled at him

02:54.000 --> 02:56.000
She liked Jonathan

02:56.000 --> 02:58.000
Hello, Martha

02:58.000 --> 03:00.000
She said

03:00.000 --> 03:02.000
She didn't smile at Martha

03:02.000 --> 03:04.000
She didn't like her

03:04.000 --> 03:06.000
I'd like some tulips

03:06.000 --> 03:08.000
Said Martha

03:08.000 --> 03:10.000
Red tulips, please

03:12.000 --> 03:14.000
There was a little girl in the shop

03:14.000 --> 03:16.000
She was very pretty with dark hair

03:16.000 --> 03:18.000
She was three years old

03:20.000 --> 03:22.000
Hello, Lana

03:22.000 --> 03:24.000
Said Martha

03:24.000 --> 03:26.000
Where are your mum and dad today?

03:26.000 --> 03:28.000
They're at the homecoming game

03:28.000 --> 03:30.000
Nell said

03:30.000 --> 03:32.000
Here are your tulips

03:32.000 --> 03:34.000
She gave them to Jonathan

03:34.000 --> 03:36.000
In the street

03:36.000 --> 03:38.000
Martha said sadly

03:38.000 --> 03:40.000
Oh, Jonathan

03:40.000 --> 03:42.000
I looked at Lana's little face

03:42.000 --> 03:44.000
And I

03:44.000 --> 03:46.000
She stopped

03:46.000 --> 03:48.000
I know Martha

03:48.000 --> 03:50.000
Said Jonathan

03:50.000 --> 03:52.000
We both want a child

03:52.000 --> 03:56.000
The meteors came closer and closer

03:56.000 --> 03:58.000
At the factory

03:58.000 --> 04:00.000
Lex was bored

04:00.000 --> 04:02.000
He walked away into a cornfield

04:02.000 --> 04:04.000
Next to the factory

04:04.000 --> 04:06.000
Lionel Luther read the papers

04:06.000 --> 04:08.000
Where do I put my name?

04:08.000 --> 04:10.000
He asked the Ross brothers

04:10.000 --> 04:12.000
He smiled

04:12.000 --> 04:16.000
The factory was his now

04:16.000 --> 04:18.000
Alone in the field

04:18.000 --> 04:20.000
Lex suddenly heard something

04:20.000 --> 04:22.000
Help me

04:22.000 --> 04:24.000
What was it?

04:24.000 --> 04:26.000
Then he heard it again

04:26.000 --> 04:28.000
Help me

04:28.000 --> 04:30.000
He walked through the corn

04:30.000 --> 04:32.000
And suddenly

04:32.000 --> 04:34.000
There was a scarecrow

04:34.000 --> 04:36.000
Lex was frightened

04:36.000 --> 04:38.000
Lex was frightened

04:38.000 --> 04:40.000
That scarecrow can talk

04:40.000 --> 04:42.000
He thought

04:42.000 --> 04:44.000
But then it wasn't a scarecrow

04:44.000 --> 04:46.000
It was a teenage boy

04:46.000 --> 04:50.000
The boy was on a big wooden pole

04:50.000 --> 04:52.000
He had no shirt

04:52.000 --> 04:56.000
There was a big red S on the front of his body

04:56.000 --> 04:58.000
Help me

04:58.000 --> 05:00.000
Please

05:00.000 --> 05:02.000
He said one more time

05:02.000 --> 05:04.000
Boom

05:04.000 --> 05:06.000
A big meteor

05:06.000 --> 05:08.000
Crashed into the cornfield

05:08.000 --> 05:10.000
Lex ran

05:10.000 --> 05:12.000
A car

05:12.000 --> 05:14.000
Stopped opposite Nell's shop on Main Street

05:14.000 --> 05:16.000
Nell took little Lana in her arms

05:16.000 --> 05:18.000
And walked out of the shop

05:18.000 --> 05:22.000
Lewis and Laura Lang were in the car

05:22.000 --> 05:24.000
Lana saw them

05:24.000 --> 05:26.000
Mommy, daddy

05:26.000 --> 05:28.000
She shouted

05:28.000 --> 05:30.000
Nell looked up

05:30.000 --> 05:32.000
And saw a big meteor in the sky

05:33.000 --> 05:35.000
Doom

05:35.000 --> 05:39.000
The meteor crashed into the Lang's car

05:39.000 --> 05:43.000
Lana's parents were dead

05:43.000 --> 05:46.000
Lionel Luther ran across the cornfield

05:46.000 --> 05:48.000
Lex, where are you?

05:48.000 --> 05:50.000
He shouted

05:50.000 --> 05:53.000
He saw some red hair on the ground

05:53.000 --> 05:56.000
Then he found his son

05:56.000 --> 05:58.000
Lex was on the ground

05:58.000 --> 06:00.000
He was very frightened

06:00.000 --> 06:03.000
But where was his beautiful red hair?

06:03.000 --> 06:05.000
He was nine years old

06:05.000 --> 06:08.000
And he now had no hair at all

06:10.000 --> 06:13.000
Jonathan and Martha Kent were on their way home

06:13.000 --> 06:17.000
Suddenly, a meteor hit the road behind them

06:17.000 --> 06:19.000
What was that, Jonathan?

06:19.000 --> 06:21.000
Asked Martha

06:21.000 --> 06:23.000
What's happening?

06:23.000 --> 06:25.000
Boom!

06:25.000 --> 06:28.000
A spaceship crashed into the road in front of them

06:28.000 --> 06:31.000
Jonathan tried to stop the car

06:31.000 --> 06:34.000
But it crashed into a cornfield

06:34.000 --> 06:36.000
When they opened their eyes

06:36.000 --> 06:38.000
They saw a boy

06:38.000 --> 06:40.000
He was about three years old

06:40.000 --> 06:43.000
And he had no clothes

06:43.000 --> 06:46.000
The boy pulled Jonathan's car door

06:46.000 --> 06:47.000
It opened

06:47.000 --> 06:50.000
Then he pulled Martha's car door

06:50.000 --> 06:52.000
It opened too

06:52.000 --> 06:56.000
Martha and Jonathan were very surprised

06:56.000 --> 06:58.000
They were soon out of the car

06:58.000 --> 07:01.000
Martha took the boy in her arms

07:01.000 --> 07:03.000
Are you okay?

07:03.000 --> 07:04.000
Asked Jonathan

07:04.000 --> 07:06.000
Yes, I'm fine

07:06.000 --> 07:09.000
You? said Martha

07:09.000 --> 07:13.000
But yes, children don't fall from the sky

07:13.000 --> 07:15.000
Jonathan said

07:15.000 --> 07:18.000
Then, where did he come from?

07:18.000 --> 07:19.000
Martha asked

07:19.000 --> 07:23.000
I don't think his mum and dad are from Kansas

07:23.000 --> 07:25.000
We can't keep him, Martha

07:25.000 --> 07:27.000
Said Jonathan

07:27.000 --> 07:29.000
What can we say to people?

07:29.000 --> 07:32.000
We found him in a cornfield?

07:32.000 --> 07:35.000
We didn't find him, Jonathan

07:35.000 --> 07:37.000
Said Martha

07:37.000 --> 07:39.000
He found us

07:39.000 --> 07:54.000
Chapter 2

07:54.000 --> 07:58.000
Special and Different

07:58.000 --> 08:01.000
Jonathan and Martha took the boy home to their farm

08:01.000 --> 08:04.000
They named him Clark

08:04.000 --> 08:07.000
They didn't tell him about his arrival

08:07.000 --> 08:10.000
They didn't tell other people either

08:10.000 --> 08:13.000
If someone asked, they said

08:13.000 --> 08:15.000
He's Martha's sister's son

08:15.000 --> 08:17.000
She died

08:17.000 --> 08:21.000
They didn't want Clark to be different from other children

08:21.000 --> 08:23.000
But he was different

08:23.000 --> 08:25.000
He was special

08:25.000 --> 08:27.000
He was very strong

08:27.000 --> 08:29.000
He was very fast

08:29.000 --> 08:31.000
Nothing hurt him

08:31.000 --> 08:33.000
When he was eight

08:33.000 --> 08:35.000
A big milk can hit his head

08:35.000 --> 08:38.000
It didn't hurt him

08:38.000 --> 08:44.000
2001, Smallville, Kansas, USA

08:44.000 --> 08:46.000
Clark sat at his computer

08:46.000 --> 08:49.000
Every morning he used the internet

08:49.000 --> 08:53.000
He wanted to find stories about special people

08:53.000 --> 08:55.000
Very strong people

08:55.000 --> 08:57.000
Very fast people

08:57.000 --> 08:59.000
Clark Kent, Martha called

08:59.000 --> 09:02.000
You're going to be late for the bus

09:02.000 --> 09:04.000
Okay, I'm coming

09:04.000 --> 09:06.000
Shouted Clark

09:06.000 --> 09:08.000
He put on his school clothes and shoes

09:08.000 --> 09:12.000
Cleaned his room and put his school books in his bag

09:12.000 --> 09:14.000
All in one minute

09:14.000 --> 09:18.000
Martha came into his room with some clothes

09:18.000 --> 09:22.000
You can wear these to the homecoming dance this weekend

09:22.000 --> 09:23.000
She said

09:23.000 --> 09:25.000
I'm not going, Mum

09:25.000 --> 09:26.000
Said Clark

09:26.000 --> 09:29.000
I haven't got a girl to go with

09:29.000 --> 09:31.000
Did you ask anyone?

09:31.000 --> 09:33.000
Martha asked

09:33.000 --> 09:35.000
No, he said

09:35.000 --> 09:37.000
He ran down to the kitchen

09:37.000 --> 09:39.000
What's that letter, son?

09:39.000 --> 09:41.000
Ask Jonathan

09:41.000 --> 09:43.000
It's for the football team

09:43.000 --> 09:45.000
Said Clark

09:45.000 --> 09:47.000
They want some new players

09:47.000 --> 09:49.000
You can't do it

09:49.000 --> 09:51.000
Said Jonathan

09:51.000 --> 09:53.000
Oh, please Dad

09:53.000 --> 09:54.000
Said Clark

09:54.000 --> 09:55.000
I can run slowly

09:55.000 --> 09:57.000
I can be careful

09:57.000 --> 09:59.000
I'm sorry Clark

09:59.000 --> 10:01.000
Said Jonathan

10:01.000 --> 10:03.000
But the answer is no

10:03.000 --> 10:05.000
I don't want to be different

10:05.000 --> 10:07.000
Shouted Clark

10:07.000 --> 10:09.000
I can never do normal things

10:09.000 --> 10:11.000
People at school think I'm a loser

10:11.000 --> 10:13.000
He ran out of the door

10:13.000 --> 10:17.000
We must tell him about the spaceship

10:17.000 --> 10:19.000
Martha said to Jonathan

10:19.000 --> 10:22.000
Clark walked to the bus stop

10:22.000 --> 10:24.000
He was late again

10:24.000 --> 10:27.000
The school bus drove off without him

10:27.000 --> 10:29.000
Oh no, he said

10:29.000 --> 10:31.000
Everything's going wrong today

10:31.000 --> 10:33.000
Suddenly

10:33.000 --> 10:35.000
He smiled a big smile

10:35.000 --> 10:38.000
He turned and ran through the field

10:38.000 --> 10:41.000
At a hundred kilometers an hour

10:41.000 --> 10:44.000
The bus arrived at school

10:44.000 --> 10:48.000
Clark's friends Pete Ross and Chloe Sullivan were on it

10:48.000 --> 10:51.000
Chloe was new in Smallville

10:51.000 --> 10:54.000
Her dad worked at Luther Corps

10:54.000 --> 10:56.000
She wrote for the school newspaper

10:56.000 --> 10:58.000
And took photos for it

10:58.000 --> 11:01.000
She was always ready with her camera

11:01.000 --> 11:04.000
Are you going to the dance with anyone?

11:04.000 --> 11:06.000
Pete asked Chloe

11:06.000 --> 11:08.000
No, not yet

11:08.000 --> 11:10.000
Said Chloe

11:10.000 --> 11:13.000
Well, if Clark doesn't ask you

11:13.000 --> 11:16.000
I'm not interested in Clark Pete

11:16.000 --> 11:18.000
She said

11:18.000 --> 11:19.000
Right

11:19.000 --> 11:21.000
Said Pete

11:21.000 --> 11:23.000
He knew that wasn't true

11:23.000 --> 11:27.000
Well, we can go to the dance together if you want

11:27.000 --> 11:28.000
He said

11:28.000 --> 11:30.000
Not boy and girl

11:30.000 --> 11:32.000
Friend and friend

11:32.000 --> 11:34.000
Suddenly Clark was there

11:34.000 --> 11:36.000
Hi you too

11:36.000 --> 11:37.000
He said

11:37.000 --> 11:41.000
Pete and Chloe were very surprised to see their friend

11:41.000 --> 11:43.000
We saw you at your farm

11:43.000 --> 11:44.000
Chloe said

11:44.000 --> 11:46.000
You weren't on the bus

11:46.000 --> 11:49.000
I came a different way

11:49.000 --> 11:50.000
Said Clark

11:50.000 --> 11:53.000
Are you ready for the football team Clark?

11:53.000 --> 11:54.000
Asked Pete

11:54.000 --> 11:56.000
I'm not going to do it

11:56.000 --> 11:58.000
Said Clark

11:58.000 --> 12:00.000
But Clark said Pete

12:00.000 --> 12:03.000
Do you want to be the scarecrow?

12:03.000 --> 12:05.000
The scarecrow

12:05.000 --> 12:07.000
Chloe said loudly

12:07.000 --> 12:09.000
What's the scarecrow?

12:09.000 --> 12:10.000
Shh

12:10.000 --> 12:11.000
Said Pete

12:11.000 --> 12:13.000
This happens here every year Chloe

12:13.000 --> 12:15.000
Before the homecoming game

12:15.000 --> 12:18.000
The football players choose someone

12:18.000 --> 12:20.000
A loser

12:20.000 --> 12:22.000
They take him to the cornfield

12:22.000 --> 12:24.000
And take all his clothes

12:24.000 --> 12:28.000
Then they write a big red S on the front of his body

12:28.000 --> 12:31.000
And they put him on a big wooden pole

12:31.000 --> 12:32.000
Said Clark

12:32.000 --> 12:33.000
So

12:33.000 --> 12:35.000
He's a scarecrow

12:35.000 --> 12:36.000
How terrible

12:36.000 --> 12:38.000
Said Chloe

12:38.000 --> 12:41.000
Then Clark saw a beautiful girl

12:41.000 --> 12:44.000
With long brown hair and a lovely smile

12:44.000 --> 12:46.000
See you later

12:46.000 --> 12:48.000
He said to his friends

12:48.000 --> 12:52.000
Clark walked across to Lana Lang

12:52.000 --> 12:54.000
He was a meter from her

12:54.000 --> 12:56.000
Suddenly he crashed to the ground

12:56.000 --> 12:58.000
His books went everywhere

12:58.000 --> 13:02.000
Why does this always happen near Lana?

13:02.000 --> 13:03.000
He thought

13:03.000 --> 13:05.000
Is it because I like her?

13:05.000 --> 13:07.000
Hi Clark

13:07.000 --> 13:08.000
Are you okay?

13:08.000 --> 13:09.000
She asked

13:09.000 --> 13:11.000
Hi Lana

13:11.000 --> 13:12.000
He said

13:12.000 --> 13:13.000
Yeah

13:13.000 --> 13:14.000
I'm fine

13:14.000 --> 13:16.000
She gave his books to him

13:16.000 --> 13:18.000
You're reading Nietzsche, huh?

13:18.000 --> 13:20.000
Are you man or Superman?

13:20.000 --> 13:22.000
I don't know

13:22.000 --> 13:23.000
Clark said

13:23.000 --> 13:25.000
They smiled

13:25.000 --> 13:27.000
Lana

13:27.000 --> 13:29.000
shouted Whitney Fordman

13:29.000 --> 13:31.000
A tall good looking student

13:31.000 --> 13:33.000
He was Lana's boyfriend

13:33.000 --> 13:36.000
Whitney was fantastic at sports

13:36.000 --> 13:38.000
He was in all the school teams

13:38.000 --> 13:41.000
He ran up and kissed Lana

13:41.000 --> 13:43.000
They walked away together

13:44.000 --> 13:45.000
Chapter 3

13:45.000 --> 13:46.000
Two terrible shocks

13:46.000 --> 13:48.000
A student looked at the photos of the school sports teams

13:48.000 --> 13:51.000
He looked at the 1989 photo

13:51.000 --> 13:55.000
You're late for your class young man?

13:55.000 --> 14:03.000
Said a student

14:03.000 --> 14:06.000
He looked at the 1989 photo

14:06.000 --> 14:09.000
You're late for your class young man?

14:09.000 --> 14:11.000
Said a student

14:11.000 --> 14:13.000
A class young man?

14:13.000 --> 14:15.000
Said a teacher behind him

14:15.000 --> 14:16.000
The student turned

14:16.000 --> 14:18.000
What's your name?

14:18.000 --> 14:19.000
Asked the teacher

14:19.000 --> 14:21.000
Are you new?

14:21.000 --> 14:25.000
Suddenly the student hit the teacher in the face

14:25.000 --> 14:28.000
A big blue electric shock

14:28.000 --> 14:29.000
Went from the student's hand

14:29.000 --> 14:31.000
Into the teacher's body

14:31.000 --> 14:34.000
The teacher crashed into the wall

14:34.000 --> 14:38.000
The student took the photo of the three happy football players

14:38.000 --> 14:40.000
And left the school

14:40.000 --> 14:42.000
I'm gonna get you

14:42.000 --> 14:44.000
He thought

14:44.000 --> 14:47.000
Lex Luthor drove his Porsche through the country

14:47.000 --> 14:50.000
To the Luther Court factory in Smallville

14:50.000 --> 14:54.000
The Smallville factory doesn't make any money

14:54.000 --> 14:56.000
Lionel Luthor said to his son

14:56.000 --> 14:58.000
Go to Smallville

14:58.000 --> 15:00.000
Make changes

15:00.000 --> 15:02.000
So Lex left Metropolis

15:02.000 --> 15:04.000
And here he was

15:04.000 --> 15:06.000
In the centre of nowhere

15:06.000 --> 15:08.000
Great

15:08.000 --> 15:10.000
Lex arrived at Luther Court

15:10.000 --> 15:12.000
He was 21 years old

15:12.000 --> 15:16.000
And he still had no hair

15:16.000 --> 15:18.000
He walked into the factory

15:18.000 --> 15:22.000
A man sat at a desk with his lunch

15:22.000 --> 15:25.000
Mr. Luthor, the man said surprised

15:25.000 --> 15:28.000
My name's Gabe Sullivan

15:28.000 --> 15:30.000
Call me Lex

15:30.000 --> 15:32.000
The workers aren't happy Lex

15:32.000 --> 15:34.000
Said Gabe

15:34.000 --> 15:36.000
They're frightened about their jobs

15:37.000 --> 15:39.000
It's okay, said Lex

15:39.000 --> 15:41.000
I want everyone to stay

15:42.000 --> 15:44.000
But your father said

15:44.000 --> 15:46.000
I'm not my father

15:46.000 --> 15:48.000
Said Lex Luthor

15:50.000 --> 15:53.000
Later, Lex drove down a small country road

15:53.000 --> 15:55.000
At a hundred kilometers an hour

15:55.000 --> 15:58.000
His car radio played loud music

15:59.000 --> 16:02.000
Not far away, Clark was on a bridge

16:02.000 --> 16:04.000
He looked into the water

16:05.000 --> 16:07.000
He thought about his life

16:07.000 --> 16:09.000
And he wasn't happy

16:09.000 --> 16:11.000
He didn't hear Lex Luthor's car

16:13.000 --> 16:15.000
Lex answered his mobile phone

16:15.000 --> 16:18.000
He didn't look at the road for a minute

16:18.000 --> 16:20.000
He drove onto the bridge

16:20.000 --> 16:22.000
Then he saw Clark

16:22.000 --> 16:24.000
He tried to stop the car

16:24.000 --> 16:26.000
But Clark was right in front of him

16:26.000 --> 16:28.000
I'm going to hit him

16:28.000 --> 16:30.000
Lex thought

16:30.000 --> 16:32.000
Their eyes met

16:32.000 --> 16:34.000
Lex's car crashed into Clark

16:34.000 --> 16:36.000
Boom

16:36.000 --> 16:39.000
The car and Clark went over the bridge

16:39.000 --> 16:41.000
And into the water

16:41.000 --> 16:43.000
Clark's eyes closed

16:43.000 --> 16:45.000
And everything went black

16:58.000 --> 17:00.000
Chapter 4

17:00.000 --> 17:02.000
The green necklace

17:04.000 --> 17:05.000
Under the water

17:05.000 --> 17:07.000
Clark opened his eyes

17:07.000 --> 17:09.000
He was okay

17:09.000 --> 17:11.000
He wasn't hurt

17:11.000 --> 17:13.000
Then he remembered the car

17:13.000 --> 17:15.000
The car

17:15.000 --> 17:17.000
He found the car with Lex in it

17:17.000 --> 17:20.000
Lex's eyes were closed

17:20.000 --> 17:22.000
Clark pulled open the door

17:22.000 --> 17:24.000
And pulled Lex out

17:24.000 --> 17:25.000
He took him in his arms

17:25.000 --> 17:27.000
And started to swim

17:28.000 --> 17:30.000
When Clark put Lex on the ground

17:30.000 --> 17:32.000
He thought he was dead

17:32.000 --> 17:35.000
Clark put his left hand on Lex's body

17:35.000 --> 17:38.000
Then he put his right hand over his left

17:38.000 --> 17:42.000
One, two, one, two

17:42.000 --> 17:44.000
One, two

17:44.000 --> 17:46.000
Come on, don't die

17:46.000 --> 17:48.000
He said

17:48.000 --> 17:50.000
Some water came out of Lex's mouth

17:50.000 --> 17:52.000
He opened his eyes

17:52.000 --> 17:54.000
And saw Clark

17:54.000 --> 17:56.000
He was very surprised

17:56.000 --> 17:58.000
But I hid you

17:58.000 --> 17:59.000
He said

17:59.000 --> 18:01.000
Well, I'm not dead

18:01.000 --> 18:03.000
Said Clark

18:03.000 --> 18:06.000
Clark looked at the bridge

18:06.000 --> 18:08.000
A car hit me

18:08.000 --> 18:10.000
At a hundred kilometers an hour

18:10.000 --> 18:12.000
I'm not hurt

18:12.000 --> 18:14.000
I am not normal

18:14.000 --> 18:16.000
He thought

18:16.000 --> 18:20.000
The police and the doctor arrived

18:20.000 --> 18:23.000
Then Jonathan Kent arrived too

18:24.000 --> 18:27.000
Jonathan put his arms around Clark

18:27.000 --> 18:29.000
Are you okay, son?

18:29.000 --> 18:30.000
He asked

18:30.000 --> 18:32.000
I'm fine, Dad

18:32.000 --> 18:33.000
Said Clark

18:33.000 --> 18:35.000
I'm Jonathan Kent

18:35.000 --> 18:37.000
This is my son

18:37.000 --> 18:39.000
Jonathan told a policeman

18:39.000 --> 18:42.000
Who was the stupid driver of the car?

18:42.000 --> 18:43.000
I was

18:43.000 --> 18:45.000
Said Lex Luther

18:45.000 --> 18:48.000
You have a very special son, Mr Kent

18:48.000 --> 18:50.000
He said

18:50.000 --> 18:52.000
You saved my life, Clark

18:52.000 --> 18:54.000
How can I thank you?

18:54.000 --> 18:56.000
Drive more slowly

18:56.000 --> 18:58.000
Said Jonathan

18:58.000 --> 19:00.000
After dinner that night

19:00.000 --> 19:04.000
Clark went up to his special room in the barn

19:04.000 --> 19:06.000
He looked at the night sky

19:06.000 --> 19:11.000
Then he looked over at the farmhouse next to the Kent's farm

19:11.000 --> 19:13.000
The front door opened

19:13.000 --> 19:15.000
And Lana Lang came out

19:15.000 --> 19:17.000
Clark smiled

19:17.000 --> 19:20.000
But then Whitney came out

19:20.000 --> 19:23.000
Whitney put his arms around Lana

19:23.000 --> 19:25.000
Are you alone tonight?

19:25.000 --> 19:26.000
He asked

19:26.000 --> 19:31.000
Yes, aren't now that Lex Luther's said Lana

19:31.000 --> 19:33.000
Did you hear about Clark?

19:33.000 --> 19:34.000
She said

19:34.000 --> 19:36.000
He saved Lex's life today

19:36.000 --> 19:39.000
Clark, Whitney said

19:39.000 --> 19:41.000
Clark Kent

19:41.000 --> 19:43.000
Yes, said Lana

19:43.000 --> 19:46.000
Sometimes people can surprise you

19:46.000 --> 19:49.000
Whitney didn't want to talk about Clark

19:49.000 --> 19:52.000
He wanted to talk about Whitney

19:52.000 --> 19:54.000
I've got a game on Saturday

19:54.000 --> 19:55.000
He said

19:55.000 --> 19:58.000
Some important people are going to be there

19:58.000 --> 19:59.000
That's great

19:59.000 --> 20:00.000
Lana said

20:00.000 --> 20:03.000
Whitney wanted to be a top football player

20:03.000 --> 20:05.000
It was his dream

20:05.000 --> 20:08.000
She gave her green necklace to him

20:08.000 --> 20:11.000
The necklace was part of a meteor

20:11.000 --> 20:13.000
A special meteor

20:13.000 --> 20:17.000
This meteor hit Lana's parents car

20:17.000 --> 20:19.000
I can't take this Lana

20:19.000 --> 20:20.000
Whitney said

20:20.000 --> 20:22.000
It means everything to you

20:22.000 --> 20:25.000
Keep it just for the game

20:25.000 --> 20:26.000
She said

20:26.000 --> 20:28.000
He put it in his jacket

20:28.000 --> 20:30.000
Then he kissed her

20:43.000 --> 20:44.000
Chapter 5

20:44.000 --> 20:46.000
The true story

20:47.000 --> 20:50.000
Tony Carrozza had a job at a car place

20:50.000 --> 20:51.000
It was evening

20:51.000 --> 20:54.000
It was almost time to go home

20:54.000 --> 20:56.000
A boy came into the shop

20:56.000 --> 20:58.000
I'm sorry

20:58.000 --> 20:59.000
Said Tony

20:59.000 --> 21:00.000
We're closed

21:00.000 --> 21:02.000
The boy said nothing

21:02.000 --> 21:04.000
Tony looked at him carefully

21:04.000 --> 21:06.000
I know you

21:06.000 --> 21:07.000
He said

21:07.000 --> 21:10.000
You were that scarecrow years ago

21:10.000 --> 21:12.000
What happened to you?

21:12.000 --> 21:14.000
Why aren't you older?

21:15.000 --> 21:17.000
The boy still said nothing

21:17.000 --> 21:19.000
Answer me stupid

21:19.000 --> 21:20.000
Said Tony

21:20.000 --> 21:22.000
I'm talking to you

21:22.000 --> 21:25.000
The boy suddenly hit Tony in the face

21:25.000 --> 21:29.000
A big blue electric shock went from his hand

21:29.000 --> 21:31.000
Into Tony Carrozza's body

21:31.000 --> 21:34.000
Tony crashed onto the floor

21:34.000 --> 21:36.000
He didn't move

21:36.000 --> 21:37.000
On the wall

21:37.000 --> 21:41.000
There was a photo of three happy football players

21:41.000 --> 21:43.000
The boy smiled

21:43.000 --> 21:45.000
And left the shop

21:45.000 --> 21:47.000
It was the day after the car crash

21:47.000 --> 21:49.000
When Clark walked into school

21:49.000 --> 21:51.000
Every student said

21:51.000 --> 21:53.000
Nice work Clark

21:53.000 --> 21:55.000
Am I at the right school?

21:55.000 --> 21:57.000
Clark asked Pete and Chloe

21:57.000 --> 22:01.000
You saved Lex Luthor's life, said Chloe

22:01.000 --> 22:04.000
This is going in the school newspaper

22:04.000 --> 22:07.000
My dad hates the luthas

22:07.000 --> 22:09.000
Said Pete

22:09.000 --> 22:13.000
Yes, but Lionel Luthor bought your dad's factory

22:13.000 --> 22:15.000
Not Lex

22:15.000 --> 22:17.000
Said Clark

22:17.000 --> 22:20.000
When Clark arrived home on the farm that afternoon

22:20.000 --> 22:24.000
He found a new red car in front of the house

22:24.000 --> 22:26.000
There was a letter on the car

22:26.000 --> 22:28.000
Clark opened it

22:28.000 --> 22:30.000
Thank you Clark

22:30.000 --> 22:31.000
He read

22:31.000 --> 22:33.000
I hope you like Red

22:33.000 --> 22:35.000
Clark looked at the car

22:35.000 --> 22:37.000
He was very excited

22:37.000 --> 22:39.000
You can't keep it Clark

22:39.000 --> 22:41.000
Jonathan said

22:41.000 --> 22:43.000
Why not?

22:43.000 --> 22:45.000
Because the luthas aren't good people

22:45.000 --> 22:47.000
They're rich thanks to Smallville

22:47.000 --> 22:51.000
They bought our friends houses and their farms

22:51.000 --> 22:54.000
Lex's father did all that, said Clark

22:54.000 --> 22:56.000
Not Lex

22:56.000 --> 22:58.000
I'm sorry Clark

22:58.000 --> 22:59.000
Jonathan said

22:59.000 --> 23:01.000
I know you're angry

23:01.000 --> 23:03.000
Angry, shouted Clark

23:03.000 --> 23:05.000
You have no idea

23:05.000 --> 23:09.000
He ran up to his room in the barn

23:09.000 --> 23:13.000
You must tell him now, Martha said

23:13.000 --> 23:16.000
Jonathan went to Clark's room

23:16.000 --> 23:19.000
He put his arms around his son

23:19.000 --> 23:23.000
I'm going to tell you the story of the day of the meteors

23:23.000 --> 23:25.000
He said

23:25.000 --> 23:27.000
He gave Clark a picture

23:27.000 --> 23:30.000
There were lots of letters and numbers on it

23:30.000 --> 23:32.000
Was it a language?

23:33.000 --> 23:36.000
I think this is from your mum and dad

23:36.000 --> 23:37.000
He said

23:37.000 --> 23:39.000
What does it say?

23:39.000 --> 23:41.000
Clark asked

23:41.000 --> 23:44.000
I have no idea, said Jonathan

23:44.000 --> 23:47.000
They came from a different world

23:47.000 --> 23:50.000
A different world, laughed Clark

23:50.000 --> 23:53.000
So I arrived in a spaceship

23:53.000 --> 23:55.000
And that's stupid

23:55.000 --> 23:58.000
Do you want to see that spaceship?

23:58.000 --> 24:00.000
Ask Jonathan

24:00.000 --> 24:02.000
It's under the barn

24:02.000 --> 24:05.000
When he saw the little spaceship

24:05.000 --> 24:07.000
Clark was very angry

24:07.000 --> 24:09.000
Why didn't you tell me this before?

24:09.000 --> 24:11.000
He shouted

24:11.000 --> 24:13.000
He ran out of the barn

24:13.000 --> 24:27.000
Chapter 6

24:27.000 --> 24:29.000
A quick kiss

24:29.000 --> 24:32.000
Lana Lang looked at the words

24:32.000 --> 24:37.000
Lewis Lang, 1957-1989

24:37.000 --> 24:42.000
Laura Lang, 1959-1989

24:43.000 --> 24:45.000
She heard something behind her

24:45.000 --> 24:46.000
Who's there?

24:46.000 --> 24:47.000
She called

24:47.000 --> 24:50.000
It's me, it's Clark

24:50.000 --> 24:51.000
He said

24:51.000 --> 24:53.000
What are you doing here?

24:53.000 --> 24:56.000
Lana looked at Clark

24:56.000 --> 24:57.000
He was nice

24:57.000 --> 25:00.000
Please don't tell anyone, she said

25:00.000 --> 25:03.000
I come here to talk to my mum and dad

25:03.000 --> 25:05.000
Is that stupid?

25:05.000 --> 25:07.000
No, it isn't stupid

25:07.000 --> 25:08.000
Clark said

25:08.000 --> 25:10.000
Do you remember them?

25:10.000 --> 25:13.000
Not very well, said Lana

25:13.000 --> 25:15.000
They died when I was three

25:15.000 --> 25:18.000
Do you want to meet them?

25:18.000 --> 25:20.000
She sat on the ground

25:20.000 --> 25:24.000
Mum, dad, this is Clark Kent

25:24.000 --> 25:26.000
She said

25:26.000 --> 25:28.000
Hi Mr. and Mrs. Lang

25:28.000 --> 25:30.000
Said Clark

25:30.000 --> 25:31.000
I'm sorry?

25:31.000 --> 25:33.000
What's that?

25:33.000 --> 25:35.000
He sat down and listened

25:35.000 --> 25:38.000
Your mum says

25:38.000 --> 25:40.000
You're never alone, Lana

25:40.000 --> 25:41.000
He said

25:41.000 --> 25:43.000
And your dad says

25:43.000 --> 25:45.000
You're beautiful

25:45.000 --> 25:47.000
Lana smiled

25:47.000 --> 25:49.000
Thank you, Clark

25:49.000 --> 25:50.000
She said

25:50.000 --> 25:52.000
Can I walk home with you?

25:52.000 --> 25:53.000
Ask Clark

25:53.000 --> 25:55.000
Yes, thanks

25:55.000 --> 25:56.000
Said Lana

25:56.000 --> 25:59.000
When they arrived at Lana's house

25:59.000 --> 26:00.000
She said

26:00.000 --> 26:03.000
We talked for a long time tonight, Clark

26:03.000 --> 26:05.000
It was nice

26:05.000 --> 26:07.000
She kissed him quickly

26:07.000 --> 26:09.000
Goodnight, Clark

26:09.000 --> 26:11.000
She ran into the house

26:11.000 --> 26:14.000
Clark was very happy

26:14.000 --> 26:17.000
But there was someone at Lana's house

26:17.000 --> 26:19.000
He saw the kiss

26:19.000 --> 26:21.000
And he was very angry

26:21.000 --> 26:24.000
It was Whitney Fordman

26:24.000 --> 26:26.000
The next day before school

26:26.000 --> 26:30.000
Clark drove the red car back to Lex Luthor's house

26:30.000 --> 26:32.000
The house was big and old

26:32.000 --> 26:34.000
The front door was open

26:34.000 --> 26:36.000
Clark walked in

26:36.000 --> 26:38.000
Hello, he shouted

26:38.000 --> 26:40.000
Is anyone at home?

26:40.000 --> 26:43.000
Clark said Lex

26:43.000 --> 26:45.000
What are you doing here?

26:45.000 --> 26:47.000
How's your new car?

26:47.000 --> 26:49.000
I love it, said Clark

26:49.000 --> 26:52.000
But I can't keep it

26:52.000 --> 26:54.000
Why not?

26:54.000 --> 26:56.000
You saved my life, Clark

26:56.000 --> 26:58.000
I want to thank you

26:58.000 --> 27:00.000
Lex said

27:00.000 --> 27:01.000
Then he said

27:01.000 --> 27:03.000
Oh, I get it

27:03.000 --> 27:05.000
Your dad doesn't like me

27:05.000 --> 27:07.000
Clark didn't say anything

27:07.000 --> 27:09.000
It's okay, said Lex

27:09.000 --> 27:11.000
I understand

27:11.000 --> 27:14.000
It's not you, said Clark

27:14.000 --> 27:17.000
He doesn't like your father

27:17.000 --> 27:19.000
Thank you for the car, Lex

27:19.000 --> 27:21.000
I'm sorry I can't keep it

27:21.000 --> 27:25.000
I changed after that crash, said Lex

27:25.000 --> 27:27.000
When I was under the water

27:27.000 --> 27:31.000
I saw my life in Smallville in a new way

27:31.000 --> 27:33.000
I can see now

27:33.000 --> 27:37.000
This isn't the end of my old life in Metropolis

27:37.000 --> 27:40.000
It's the start of my new life here

27:40.000 --> 27:42.000
So thank you, Clark

27:42.000 --> 27:45.000
I hope we can be friends for a long time

27:58.000 --> 28:00.000
Chapter 7

28:00.000 --> 28:02.000
This year's Scarecrow

28:04.000 --> 28:06.000
When school finished that afternoon

28:06.000 --> 28:08.000
Chloe and Pete went into town

28:08.000 --> 28:12.000
There were people and police cars in front of one of the shops

28:12.000 --> 28:14.000
And a man was on the ground

28:14.000 --> 28:16.000
What happened here?

28:16.000 --> 28:18.000
Ask Chloe

28:18.000 --> 28:20.000
It's Freddy Post

28:20.000 --> 28:23.000
He had a big electric shock, said a man

28:23.000 --> 28:25.000
Chloe turned to Pete

28:25.000 --> 28:29.000
He's the third one this week, she said

28:29.000 --> 28:32.000
And here's something interesting

28:32.000 --> 28:37.000
They were all in the school football team in 1989

28:37.000 --> 28:40.000
Pete looked at the people by the body

28:40.000 --> 28:42.000
He saw a teenage boy

28:42.000 --> 28:45.000
Who's that boy? he asked

28:45.000 --> 28:48.000
I don't know, said Chloe

28:48.000 --> 28:51.000
She quickly took a photo of him

28:51.000 --> 28:53.000
The two friends walked back to the school

28:53.000 --> 28:56.000
And went to the newspaper room

28:56.000 --> 29:01.000
I'm going to put this photo into the computer, she said

29:01.000 --> 29:04.000
Can you find the 1989 year book, Pete?

29:04.000 --> 29:09.000
A few minutes later, Pete sat next to Chloe with the book

29:09.000 --> 29:11.000
Chloe, look, he said

29:11.000 --> 29:14.000
This boy, twelve years ago

29:14.000 --> 29:17.000
His name's Jeremy Creek

29:17.000 --> 29:21.000
Chloe looked at the book and then at her photo

29:21.000 --> 29:24.000
It's the same person, she said

29:24.000 --> 29:27.000
And he's the same age

29:27.000 --> 29:29.000
That's interesting

29:30.000 --> 29:33.000
Chloe and Pete used the internet and wrote emails

29:33.000 --> 29:35.000
They found old newspapers

29:35.000 --> 29:38.000
I'm going to find Clark, said Pete

29:38.000 --> 29:41.000
We must tell him about this

29:41.000 --> 29:44.000
Pete came back with Clark

29:44.000 --> 29:49.000
Clark looked at the two photos of Jeremy Creek

29:49.000 --> 29:54.000
Jeremy had a big electric shock twelve years ago, said Chloe

29:54.000 --> 29:57.000
He was in hospital for twelve years

29:57.000 --> 30:01.000
A few days ago, he woke up and ran away

30:01.000 --> 30:06.000
So, why is he back in Smallville, asked Clark?

30:06.000 --> 30:09.000
Why is he giving electric shocks to people?

30:09.000 --> 30:12.000
Because twelve years ago, Pete said

30:12.000 --> 30:15.000
They put him on a pole in a field

30:15.000 --> 30:18.000
He was that year's scarecrow

30:18.000 --> 30:23.000
The meteor was crashed into Smallville that day, said Chloe

30:23.000 --> 30:26.000
Oh no, thought Clark

30:26.000 --> 30:28.000
All this happened because of me

30:28.000 --> 30:32.000
That was the day of my arrival

30:32.000 --> 30:35.000
He looked at a photo in one of the old newspapers

30:35.000 --> 30:37.000
It was a little girl

30:37.000 --> 30:40.000
She had a terrible look on her face

30:40.000 --> 30:42.000
It said under the photo

30:42.000 --> 30:45.000
Meteor hits mom and dad

30:45.000 --> 30:48.000
So, what do you think Clark?

30:48.000 --> 30:50.000
Ask Chloe

30:50.000 --> 30:53.000
Clark knew that little face in the photo

30:53.000 --> 30:57.000
Oh no, Lana

30:57.000 --> 31:00.000
Why didn't you tell me about this before?

31:00.000 --> 31:01.000
He shouted

31:01.000 --> 31:03.000
I did this

31:03.000 --> 31:06.000
He ran from the room

31:06.000 --> 31:09.000
In front of the school, he met Whitney

31:09.000 --> 31:11.000
Hi Clark, said Whitney

31:11.000 --> 31:13.000
I'm looking for you

31:13.000 --> 31:15.000
You're this year's scarecrow

31:15.000 --> 31:19.000
Leave me alone, Whitney, said Clark angrily

31:19.000 --> 31:20.000
Or I'm going to

31:20.000 --> 31:22.000
You're going to what?

31:22.000 --> 31:23.000
Said Whitney

31:23.000 --> 31:25.000
Come on Clark, hit me

31:25.000 --> 31:27.000
He took off his jacket

31:27.000 --> 31:30.000
Clark moved nearer to Whitney

31:30.000 --> 31:32.000
But he suddenly started to fall

31:32.000 --> 31:37.000
He saw Lana's green necklace under Whitney's open t-shirt

31:37.000 --> 31:39.000
What's between you and Lana?

31:39.000 --> 31:41.000
shouted Whitney

31:41.000 --> 31:43.000
You can have her necklace

31:43.000 --> 31:46.000
He took off the necklace and put it on Clark

31:46.000 --> 31:48.000
But you can't have Lana

31:48.000 --> 31:51.000
I'm taking her to the dance tonight

31:51.000 --> 31:53.000
Clark didn't feel well

31:53.000 --> 31:55.000
He tried to move

31:55.000 --> 31:57.000
And then everything went black

31:57.000 --> 32:01.000
Whitney and two of his friends put him in a car

32:01.000 --> 32:04.000
Jeremy Creek watched everything

32:04.000 --> 32:08.000
And he remembered this day 12 years ago

32:19.000 --> 32:22.000
Chapter 8

32:22.000 --> 32:25.000
A big red S

32:25.000 --> 32:27.000
Clark woke up

32:27.000 --> 32:30.000
He was in a cornfield on a pole

32:30.000 --> 32:32.000
He was very cold

32:32.000 --> 32:35.000
It was night and it was October

32:35.000 --> 32:37.000
He looked down

32:37.000 --> 32:40.000
There was a big red S on the front of his body

32:40.000 --> 32:42.000
He tried to move his arms

32:42.000 --> 32:44.000
I can't move

32:44.000 --> 32:46.000
What's wrong with me?

32:46.000 --> 32:47.000
He thought

32:47.000 --> 32:49.000
It's the necklace

32:49.000 --> 32:53.000
Suddenly there was a boy in front of him

32:53.000 --> 32:56.000
It hurts, said the boy

32:56.000 --> 32:58.000
I remember that

32:58.000 --> 33:01.000
Your Jeremy Creek said Clark

33:01.000 --> 33:05.000
No, Jeremy Creek died 12 years ago

33:05.000 --> 33:07.000
Said the boy

33:07.000 --> 33:09.000
He started to walk away

33:09.000 --> 33:11.000
Where are you going?

33:12.000 --> 33:13.000
Asked Clark

33:13.000 --> 33:15.000
To the school dance

33:15.000 --> 33:16.000
Said Jeremy

33:16.000 --> 33:19.000
I didn't go in 1989

33:19.000 --> 33:21.000
Please help me

33:21.000 --> 33:22.000
Said Clark

33:22.000 --> 33:24.000
No, Jeremy said

33:24.000 --> 33:26.000
You stay here

33:26.000 --> 33:28.000
I don't want to hurt you

33:28.000 --> 33:31.000
Jeremy walked down the road

33:31.000 --> 33:34.000
Lex Luthor drove by and saw him

33:34.000 --> 33:36.000
I know that boy

33:36.000 --> 33:38.000
He thought

33:38.000 --> 33:39.000
But how?

33:39.000 --> 33:40.000
From where?

33:41.000 --> 33:43.000
He stopped the car

33:43.000 --> 33:45.000
Then he remembered the field 12 years ago

33:45.000 --> 33:47.000
The boy on the pole

33:47.000 --> 33:49.000
The big red S

33:49.000 --> 33:51.000
He got out of the car

33:51.000 --> 33:53.000
And went into the field

33:53.000 --> 33:54.000
Help me

33:54.000 --> 33:55.000
He heard

33:55.000 --> 33:57.000
Help me please

33:57.000 --> 33:59.000
It's not possible

33:59.000 --> 34:00.000
Lex thought

34:00.000 --> 34:02.000
Then he saw him

34:02.000 --> 34:04.000
Clark, he shouted

34:04.000 --> 34:06.000
Lex helped Clark

34:06.000 --> 34:09.000
Clark pulled off the necklace

34:09.000 --> 34:11.000
You need a doctor Clark

34:11.000 --> 34:12.000
Lex said

34:12.000 --> 34:14.000
Without the necklace

34:14.000 --> 34:17.000
Clark was suddenly Clark again

34:17.000 --> 34:19.000
He didn't need a doctor

34:19.000 --> 34:20.000
I'm okay

34:20.000 --> 34:22.000
Thanks Lex

34:22.000 --> 34:23.000
He said

34:23.000 --> 34:26.000
He found his clothes and ran into the night

34:26.000 --> 34:29.000
Lex saw the necklace on the ground

34:29.000 --> 34:31.000
He put it in his jacket

34:31.000 --> 34:33.000
And walked back to his car

34:34.000 --> 34:36.000
At the school dance

34:36.000 --> 34:37.000
The band played

34:37.000 --> 34:39.000
Everyone danced

34:39.000 --> 34:41.000
Jeremy Creek didn't dance

34:41.000 --> 34:43.000
He was behind the school building

34:43.000 --> 34:46.000
He opened the door of a large box

34:46.000 --> 34:48.000
Water, it said

34:48.000 --> 34:51.000
They're all going to die now

34:51.000 --> 34:53.000
He thought

34:53.000 --> 34:55.000
Suddenly Clark was behind him

34:55.000 --> 34:57.000
Stop this now Jeremy

34:57.000 --> 34:58.000
He said

34:58.000 --> 35:00.000
You said Jeremy

35:00.000 --> 35:02.000
What are you doing here?

35:02.000 --> 35:05.000
You're not going to hurt my friends

35:05.000 --> 35:06.000
Said Clark

35:06.000 --> 35:08.000
You don't understand

35:08.000 --> 35:09.000
Said Jeremy

35:09.000 --> 35:12.000
I'm doing this for you and the others

35:12.000 --> 35:14.000
No more scarecrows

35:14.000 --> 35:16.000
No Jeremy

35:16.000 --> 35:17.000
Stop it

35:17.000 --> 35:18.000
Said Clark

35:18.000 --> 35:20.000
Jeremy hit Clark in the face

35:20.000 --> 35:22.000
But he had a surprise

35:22.000 --> 35:24.000
Clark wasn't hurt

35:24.000 --> 35:27.000
There was a car next to Jeremy

35:27.000 --> 35:29.000
He opened the door and started it

35:29.000 --> 35:31.000
He drove at Clark

35:31.000 --> 35:34.000
Clark put his arms in front of him

35:34.000 --> 35:36.000
But Jeremy didn't stop

35:36.000 --> 35:38.000
Clark was on the front of the car

35:38.000 --> 35:40.000
When it hit the water box

35:40.000 --> 35:42.000
There was water everywhere

35:42.000 --> 35:45.000
It gave Jeremy a big electric shock

35:45.000 --> 35:47.000
His body was blue

35:47.000 --> 35:49.000
Then everything was quiet

35:50.000 --> 35:52.000
Clark pulled the car door

35:52.000 --> 35:53.000
It opened

35:53.000 --> 35:55.000
Are you okay?

35:55.000 --> 35:56.000
He asked

35:56.000 --> 35:58.000
Who are you?

35:58.000 --> 35:59.000
Asked Jeremy

35:59.000 --> 36:01.000
I want to go home

36:02.000 --> 36:05.000
Clark watched the end of the homecoming dance

36:05.000 --> 36:08.000
Lana and Whitney danced in the centre of the room

36:08.000 --> 36:10.000
Then they kissed

36:10.000 --> 36:12.000
A long kiss

36:12.000 --> 36:14.000
Clark was sad

36:14.000 --> 36:16.000
He turned and left

36:17.000 --> 36:20.000
There were three cars in a line in the car park

36:20.000 --> 36:23.000
That's Whitney's car and his friend's cars

36:23.000 --> 36:25.000
Clark thought

36:25.000 --> 36:27.000
He had an idea

36:27.000 --> 36:29.000
He took one car

36:29.000 --> 36:31.000
And put it on top of another one

36:31.000 --> 36:33.000
Then he took the third car

36:33.000 --> 36:35.000
And put it on top of the other two

36:35.000 --> 36:37.000
He waited

36:37.000 --> 36:40.000
When students came out and saw the cars

36:40.000 --> 36:42.000
They laughed

36:42.000 --> 36:44.000
Then Whitney came out

36:44.000 --> 36:46.000
With his arm around Lana

36:46.000 --> 36:48.000
He saw his car

36:48.000 --> 36:50.000
Who did this to my car?

36:50.000 --> 36:52.000
He shouted angrily

36:52.000 --> 36:53.000
Everyone laughed

36:53.000 --> 36:55.000
And Lana smiled

36:59.000 --> 37:01.000
I want to go home

37:01.000 --> 37:03.000
I want to go home

37:03.000 --> 37:05.000
I want to go home

37:05.000 --> 37:07.000
I want to go home

37:07.000 --> 37:08.000
I want to go home

37:08.000 --> 37:09.000
Epilogue

37:09.000 --> 37:11.000
Thanks for the dance

37:11.000 --> 37:13.000
Clark

37:13.000 --> 37:15.000
Called Jonathan when he came home

37:15.000 --> 37:17.000
Lex was here

37:17.000 --> 37:19.000
This is for you

37:19.000 --> 37:21.000
He gave Clark a small box

37:21.000 --> 37:23.000
And a letter

37:23.000 --> 37:25.000
Lana's necklace was in the box

37:25.000 --> 37:27.000
Clark read the letter

37:28.000 --> 37:31.000
I found this necklace in the cornfield, Clark

37:31.000 --> 37:33.000
We're friends now

37:33.000 --> 37:35.000
So please keep this box

37:35.000 --> 37:38.000
My mother gave it to me many years ago

37:38.000 --> 37:40.000
It's very special

37:40.000 --> 37:42.000
Lex

37:42.000 --> 37:45.000
Clark opened the box and saw the necklace

37:48.000 --> 37:50.000
He didn't feel well

37:50.000 --> 37:52.000
He closed the box again

37:52.000 --> 37:54.000
And he was okay

37:54.000 --> 37:56.000
It was a special box

37:57.000 --> 37:59.000
I must remember that

37:59.000 --> 38:00.000
He thought

38:01.000 --> 38:02.000
Hello Clark

38:02.000 --> 38:05.000
It was Lana in his room in the barn

38:05.000 --> 38:07.000
Lana, he said, surprised

38:07.000 --> 38:09.000
What are you doing here?

38:09.000 --> 38:13.000
You didn't come to the dance, she said

38:13.000 --> 38:16.000
She walked up to him and put her arms around him

38:16.000 --> 38:18.000
Let's dance now

38:19.000 --> 38:21.000
They danced to the music

38:21.000 --> 38:23.000
Clark closed his eyes

38:23.000 --> 38:25.000
Suddenly he heard a car

38:25.000 --> 38:27.000
He opened his eyes

38:27.000 --> 38:29.000
Lana wasn't there

38:29.000 --> 38:31.000
It was a daydream

38:32.000 --> 38:34.000
He looked through the window

38:34.000 --> 38:36.000
A car arrived at Lana's house

38:36.000 --> 38:38.000
The necklace

38:38.000 --> 38:41.000
Clark took it to Lana's house

38:41.000 --> 38:43.000
He put it on her front door

38:43.000 --> 38:45.000
He was back in his room

38:45.000 --> 38:47.000
Before Lana opened the car door

38:47.000 --> 38:49.000
He moved faster than the wind

38:49.000 --> 38:51.000
And nobody saw him

38:51.000 --> 38:54.000
When Lana arrived at her front door

38:54.000 --> 38:56.000
She saw the necklace

38:56.000 --> 38:58.000
She took it and put it on

38:58.000 --> 39:01.000
Oh Whitney, you are fantastic

39:01.000 --> 39:03.000
She thought

39:03.000 --> 39:05.000
Goodnight Lana

39:05.000 --> 39:07.000
Clark said quietly

39:07.000 --> 39:09.000
Thanks for the dance

